  "body": "### Description\r\nBlob Transactions Not Re-added to Transaction Pool During Reorg. This happens because we deserialise the transaction from the block during the reorg. At this stage, the RLP encoded version of blobs does not contain the blobs with commitments data, causing the transaction to fail the transaction pool validation.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Include a blob transaction in a block.\r\n2. Trigger a reorg.\r\n3. Notice that the blob transaction is not returned to the transaction pool.\r\n\r\nThis issue is reproduced by the `shouldNotReAddBlobTxsWhenReorgHappens` test.\r\n\r\n**Expected behaviour:** \r\nDuring a reorg, blob transactions should be re-added to the transaction pool to ensure no transactions are lost, providing a consistent user experience. This should occur even though the deserialisation process does not include the blobs with commitment data.\r\n\r\n**Actual behaviour:** \r\nWhen a reorg occurs, blob transactions are not added back to the transaction pool.",
